The paper discusses the Quick, Draw! Dataset, which is a machine learning dataset. The paper specifically focuses on the quality of the drawings in the dataset, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the dataset consists of drawings, which suggests that it could also belong to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of a neural network for classification, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential use of the dataset for research, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
